// Semantic direction:
// vae_reparametrisering enables gradient flow: z = μ + ε*σ where ε ~ N(0,I).
// vae_elbo is the Evidence Lower BOund: E[log p(x|z)] - KL(q(z|x) || p(z)).
// vae_kl_divergens penalizes deviation from the N(0,I) prior in latent space.
// beta_vae strengthens the KL term (beta > 1) to learn disentangled representations.
// vq_vae uses discrete latent codes via vector quantization; codebook is updated with EMA.
// wgan_gradient_straff enforces the Lipschitz constraint by penalizing gradients > 1.
// spektral_normalisering_gan divides each weight matrix by its largest singular value.
// mode_kollaps is when the generator produces only a few high-quality samples.
// ddpm forward process: x_t = √ᾱ_t * x_0 + √(1-ᾱ_t) * ε, where ε ~ N(0,I).
// ddpm backward: neural network predicts ε (or x_0) to reverse the diffusion.
// ddim allows fewer denoising steps via a non-Markovian reverse process.
// score_matching trains a network to predict ∇_x log p_t(x) for each noise level t.
// flow_matching directly regresses the velocity field of an ODE from noise to data.
// ldm_enkoder/dekoder compress images into a lower-dimensional latent for efficient diffusion.
// classifier_free_guidance: ε̃ = (1+w)*ε(x,c) - w*ε(x) for sharp conditional generation.
// lora_adaptor adds low-rank update matrices to frozen weights for efficient fine-tuning.

// Primitive flow:
// VAE: enkod(x) -> μ, log_var -> z = μ + ε*exp(log_var/2)
//   dekod(z) -> x_rekonstruert -> tap = MSE(x, x_r) + β*KL(N(μ,σ²)||N(0,1))
// DDPM trening: x_0 fra data -> sample t ~ U[1,T], ε ~ N(0,I)
//   x_t = √ᾱ_t*x_0 + √(1-ᾱ_t)*ε -> prediker ε̂ = nettverk(x_t, t)
//   tap = ||ε - ε̂||²
// DDPM sampling: x_T ~ N(0,I)
//   for t = T,T-1,...,1: x_{t-1} = μ_θ(x_t,t) + σ_t*z -> returner x_0
// CFG: ε̃ = ε(x_t, tekst) + w*(ε(x_t, tekst) - ε(x_t, tom))

// This defines generative models: VAE with reparameterization trick, β-VAE, VQ-VAE,
// GAN training with Wasserstein distance and gradient penalty, normalizing flows,
// DDPM diffusion with DDIM fast sampling, latent diffusion with classifier-free guidance,
// and efficient fine-tuning with LoRA.
